Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Situated just off of Interstate 80 in Reno’s entertainment district, The Reno City Center is located less than a block from Reno’s AAA baseball park and accompanying Freight House District, Reno’s City Hall, and less than a mile from the University of Nevada Reno

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Nested in downtown Reno, just off the iconic Reno Arch landmark, is the Reno City Center Project. The project is composed of two urban blocks, featuring layers of architectural history arranged in a series of podiums and towers reaching high to the sky and connecting strongly to the surrounding network of streets.   It is the largest redevelopment project in Reno’s history. 

The mixed-use development consists of ground floor restaurants and retail with 105,000 square feet of contiguous office space spread across three floors.  There will also be 530 apartment units including top floor penthouse suites that boast tremendous views of the surrounding Sierra Nevada mountain range.  The new urban garden off the corner of Virginia Street and Commercial Row, provides much needed respite for the dense urbanity of Reno. This essential green oasis creates excitement and outdoor congregation areas for live music, taverns, coffee, ice cream parlors, fitness and storefronts. The new park cradles not only our development, but the urban network at large. It’s truly the live, work, play project that defines Reno. 

The office space options range from 5,000 SF to 105,000 SF, with large windows newly cut into the building pouring natural light into the warm shell space.  Large onsite parking garages provide ample parking to the building allowing for significant employee density in the space.  The project is connected to triple redundant fiber loops that offer extremely highspeed connectivity.  There are multiple redundant power systems in place providing back up power to the entire project.  Building signage and branding opportunities are available.  Turn-key tenant improvement packages are available. 

Project sits in the heart of Downtown Reno, within walking distance to the University of Nevada, the Reno Aces AAA baseball stadium, the Truckee Riverwalk District and a whole host of retail and dining amenities.  Come be part of Reno City Center, opening January 2022.  

*Information is subject to change and not guaranteed.

Surrounding Mayberry Gardens is a 30 acre park like setting unlikely any other campus in the area. To the West of the project sits beautifully manicured Besty Caughlin Donnelly Park with walking paths through mature landscaping. Adjacent to the South and East of the project is deed restricted agriculture land, providing a nature preserve type feel surrounding the campus.  Mayberry Gardens itself is considered a historical property, with input into the design and development of the project provided by the Reno Historical Society.
